      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"super healthy\" claims are fine for general wellness, but when you're on prescription medication, those interactions become serious business. Even a small amount of grapefruit juice can have a significant impact on how your atorvastatin is metabolized, so there is no \"little bit\" that is safe. For optimal results and to ensure your medication works as intended, you must avoid it completely.",
